to play music.

740
00:53:24,550 --> 00:53:26,679
I did not want him to, but...

741
00:53:27,687 --> 00:53:29,281
Do you have
any children, Mr. Vale?

742
00:53:29,356 --> 00:53:31,519
A son. He lives in London.

743
00:53:31,591 --> 00:53:33,619
And your wife?

744
00:53:33,694 --> 00:53:35,596
My wife passed away.

745
00:53:35,662 --> 00:53:36,652
I'm sorry.

746
00:53:43,638 --> 00:53:44,628
That's it.

747
00:53:46,341 --> 00:53:48,675
- This is where the prison is?
- Mm-hmm.

748
00:53:48,743 --> 00:53:50,770
It doesn't look like a prison.

749
00:53:50,845 --> 00:53:52,336
I think that's the point.

750
00:53:54,682 --> 00:53:56,447
How many people are in there?

751
00:53:56,518 --> 00:53:58,385
Tarek said about 300.

752
00:54:00,021 --> 00:54:01,456
There's, uh...

753
00:54:01,523 --> 00:54:03,015
There's a coffee shop on that corner.

754
00:54:03,292 --> 00:54:05,023
- It's not very nice.
- I'll wait there.

755
00:54:41,899 --> 00:54:43,994
Walter. I thought you were leaving.

756
00:54:44,068 --> 00:54:45,058
I was.

757
00:54:47,406 --> 00:54:48,806
Tarek, your mother is here.

758
00:54:48,873 --> 00:54:51,002
