801
00:57:53,268 --> 00:57:55,762
Please. I would like you to stay.

802
00:57:56,773 --> 00:57:57,763
Thank you.

803
00:57:58,774 --> 00:57:59,935
But I will manage.

804
00:58:04,614 --> 00:58:06,049
Good-bye.

805
00:58:06,115 --> 00:58:07,242
Good-bye.

806
00:58:24,301 --> 00:58:26,294
Um... Mrs... Mrs. Khalil?

807
00:58:28,305 --> 00:58:29,295
Please.

808
00:58:30,642 --> 00:58:32,578
I was with Tarek
when he was arrested.

809
00:58:32,644 --> 00:58:35,582
He was in the subway
in the first place because of me.

810
00:58:35,647 --> 00:58:36,637
So...

811
00:58:37,649 --> 00:58:38,878
please.

812
00:58:39,884 --> 00:58:41,319
Even if it's just for one night.

813
00:58:54,834 --> 00:58:57,328
Um, the bathroom is across the hall.

814
00:58:58,337 --> 00:58:59,270
Thank you, Mr. Vale.

815
00:58:59,338 --> 00:59:02,276
No. Call me Walter.

816
00:59:02,341 --> 00:59:03,331
And I'm Mouna.

817
00:59:04,845 --> 00:59:06,576
So... do you need anything else?

818
00:59:06,646 --> 00:59:07,739
No, thank you.

819
00:59:09,182 --> 00:59:11,278
Well... good night.

820
00:59:11,351 --> 00:59:12,341
Good night.

821
00:59:51,059 --> 00:59:52,220
Okay?

822
00:59:57,332 --> 00:59:58,391
Bye.

823
01:00:10,413 --> 01:00:12,280
Oh. Good morning.

824
01:00:12,349 --> 01:00:13,282
Morning.

825
01:00:13,349 --> 01:00:14,408
Mmhh...

826
01:00:19,423 --> 01:00:20,857
Tarek says hello.

827
01:00:21,926 --> 01:00:23,361
How is he?

828
01:00:23,427 --> 01:00:24,919
I can't really tell.

829
01:00:28,432 --> 01:00:30,368
He wants me to leave.

830
01:00:33,772 --> 01:00:37,212
Well... you're welcome to stay here
as long as you need to.

831
01:00:37,275 --> 01:00:38,208
Thank you.

832
01:00:38,276 --> 01:00:39,972
That's very generous of you.

833
01:00:40,046 --> 01:00:42,882
Well... thank you for the paper.

834
01:00:42,948 --> 01:00:43,973
You're welcome.

835
01:01:02,468 --> 01:01:05,406
Do you spend a lot of time in the city?

836
01:01:05,471 --> 01:01:08,238
No, no. Not really.

837
01:01:08,307 --> 01:01:11,405
I'm just here
presenting a paper at a conference.

838
01:01:11,478 --> 01:01:13,243
Well...

839
01:01:13,313 --> 01:01:14,246
You wrote it?

840
01:01:14,314 --> 01:01:15,304
Mm-hmm.

841
01:01:16,483 --> 01:01:17,815
Congratulations.

842
01:01:22,322 --> 01:01:24,258
I co-authored it, really.

843
01:01:31,132 --> 01:01:32,498
And what happened after the hearing?

844
01:01:33,735 --> 01:01:35,831
We appealed. It took two years.

845
01:01:35,904 --> 01:01:37,202
And your appeal was denied?

846
01:01:37,272 --> 01:01:38,764
Yes.

847
01:01:38,841 --> 01:01:41,107
And did they send you
your bag-and-baggage letter?

848
01:01:41,176 --> 01:01:42,907
- No.
- What's that?

849
01:01:42,977 --> 01:01:45,949
Basically, it tells you
where to show up and be deported.

850
01:01:46,014 --> 01:01:47,004
But you didn't receive it?

851
01:01:48,184 --> 01:01:50,279
No. I would remember this.

852
01:01:50,352 --> 01:01:51,786
Did you move?

853
01:01:51,854 --> 01:01:53,380
Eventually, we had to.

854
01:01:53,455 --> 01:01:55,448
But we had our mail advanced.

855
01:01:55,524 --> 01:01:58,462
Is it possible that it
just never got there?

856
01:01:58,528 --> 01:01:59,962
Yeah, it's happened before.

857
01:02:00,029 --> 01:02:02,466
And pre-9/11, it wasn't much of a priority
trackin' people down,

858
01:02:02,532 --> 01:02:06,027
but if you got it and you just ignored it,
then there's nothing I can do.

859
01:02:09,206 --> 01:02:11,142
So... you can help him.

860
01:02:11,207 --> 01:02:12,972
I'm gonna try.

861
01:02:13,044 --> 01:02:14,775
But you should know it's still a long shot.

862
01:02:14,845 --> 01:02:16,245
The government's approach
has changed radically.

863
01:02:16,313 --> 01:02:17,475
It's very black and white now.

864
01:02:17,548 --> 01:02:19,073
Either you belong, or you don't.

865
01:02:19,150 --> 01:02:21,986
Tarek's lucky.
Most of them don't even have lawyers.

866
01:02:22,052 --> 01:02:23,282
Lucky.

867
01:02:23,354 --> 01:02:24,913
Relatively speaking.

868
01:02:24,990 --> 01:02:26,424
We just have to move quickly

869
01:02:26,491 --> 01:02:28,484
to get an emergency stay,
and then we'll stick with a motion

870
01:02:28,559 --> 01:02:30,290
to reopen, pending his green card application.

871
01:02:30,361 --> 01:02:31,351
Yeah?

872
01:02:33,197 --> 01:02:34,130
Okay.

873
01:02:35,199 --> 01:02:36,964
Can you explain
what that means, please?

874
01:02:37,034 --> 01:02:38,833
Actually, I don't have
the time right now.

875
01:02:38,904 --> 01:02:41,205
I'm sorry.
I have to be in court very shortly.

876
01:02:41,273 --> 01:02:42,502
How long will he be in detention?

877
01:02:42,574 --> 01:02:46,344
I can't predict that. I am sorry,
but I am gonna have to wrap this up.

878
01:02:46,411 --> 01:02:49,578
Do you have any children, Mr. Shah?

879
01:02:51,250 --> 01:02:53,517
Yeah. Two kids.

880
01:02:53,586 --> 01:02:55,214
And for what it's worth,
my uncle was deported

881
01:02:55,288 --> 01:02:57,520
after raising a family here for 23 years.

882
01:02:58,525 --> 01:03:01,520
If I can get your son out... I will.

883
01:03:02,830 --> 01:03:03,820
Thank you.

884
01:03:08,569 --> 01:03:09,559
Where are you from?

885
01:03:10,604 --> 01:03:11,594
Queens.

886
01:03:14,275 --> 01:03:15,538
Which one is she?

887
01:03:15,609 --> 01:03:16,542
The one closest to us.

888
01:03:16,610 --> 01:03:18,512
That black woman?

889
01:03:18,579 --> 01:03:19,512
Mm-hmm.

890
01:03:19,580 --> 01:03:20,513
That is Zainab?

891
01:03:20,581 --> 01:03:21,571
Mm-hmm.

892
01:03:23,952 --> 01:03:25,284
She's very black.

893
01:03:26,287 --> 01:03:27,277
Mm-hmm.

894
01:03:35,463 --> 01:03:36,590
Zainab.

895
01:03:37,967 --> 01:03:39,458
Oh. Hi, Walter.

896
01:03:39,534 --> 01:03:41,903
Uh, Zainab, this is Mouna Khalil...

897
01:03:41,971 --> 01:03:43,565
Tarek's mother.

898
01:03:43,639 --> 01:03:44,902
- Oh...
- Hello, Zainab.

899
01:03:44,974 --> 01:03:46,237
Oh, I...

900
01:03:46,309 --> 01:03:48,438
It's a pleasure
to meet you, Mrs. Khalil.

901
01:03:48,511 --> 01:03:49,501
You, too.

902
01:03:50,546 --> 01:03:52,983
Uh... I'm s... I'm sorry.

903
01:03:53,049 --> 01:03:54,574
I... I didn't know
you were coming.

904
01:03:54,650 --> 01:03:56,643
Neither did I.

905
01:04:00,657 --> 01:04:02,923
Your jewelry is very nice.

906
01:04:02,993 --> 01:04:04,257
Oh.

907
01:04:04,327 --> 01:04:05,556
Oh, thank you.

908
01:04:08,665 --> 01:04:11,228
Do you think we can go out
for a cup of tea sometime?

909
01:04:11,301 --> 01:04:13,271
Oh... yeah.

910
01:04:13,336 --> 01:04:14,599
We could go right now.

911
01:04:14,672 --> 01:04:17,610
I... I am...
I'm just watching Zev's table,

912
01:04:17,675 --> 01:04:19,907
but I... um...

913
01:04:19,977 --> 01:04:23,678
I just need to... find someone to...

914
01:04:30,521 --> 01:04:31,614
Hey.

915
01:04:31,690 --> 01:04:32,680
Hi.

916
01:04:36,695 --> 01:04:38,220
Is it a necklace?

917
01:04:38,297 --> 01:04:39,424
I think so.

918
01:04:41,201 --> 01:04:42,692
I like that one in the front.

919
01:04:44,370 --> 01:04:45,360
Um...

920
01:04:46,505 --> 01:04:47,700
It's all handmade.

921
01:04:49,375 --> 01:04:50,400
Ooh.

922
01:04:51,510 --> 01:04:54,483
I've lived here for two years,

923
01:04:54,547 --> 01:04:57,177
and I was in France
for a year before that.

924
01:04:58,384 --> 01:04:59,477
Do you miss home?

925
01:04:59,552 --> 01:05:01,989
Yes, sometimes.

926
01:05:03,256 --> 01:05:04,724
But I don't want to live there.

927
01:05:06,559 --> 01:05:07,721
Do you miss Syria?

928
01:05:10,064 --> 01:05:11,431
Sometimes, too.

929
01:05:13,067 --> 01:05:15,003
I miss Damascus...

930
01:05:15,069 --> 01:05:16,094
the smell.

931
01:05:18,406 --> 01:05:20,239
But this is my home now.

932
01:05:22,410 --> 01:05:23,743
When did you meet Walter?

933
01:05:24,012 --> 01:05:26,175
Walter? Uh...

934
01:05:26,248 --> 01:05:28,651
about ten days ago.

935
01:05:28,717 --> 01:05:31,051
Ten days? That's all?

936
01:05:31,118 --> 01:05:32,519
Mm-hmm.

937
01:05:33,755 --> 01:05:35,520
How did you meet him?

938
01:05:35,590 --> 01:05:36,580
Uh...

939
01:05:37,759 --> 01:05:39,490
through Tarek's friend.

940
01:05:39,561 --> 01:05:42,032
Ivan. That's how we
ended up living there.

941
01:05:42,098 --> 01:05:44,159
You live there, too?

942
01:05:45,301 --> 01:05:46,770
Just for a little while.

943
01:05:47,770 --> 01:05:48,760
Oh.

944
01:05:56,279 --> 01:05:58,716
So... have you spoken to Tarek?

945
01:05:58,782 --> 01:06:00,546
Yes.

946
01:06:00,617 --> 01:06:02,210
He called me this morning.

947
01:06:02,285 --> 01:06:04,016
He sounded in a good spirit.

948
01:06:06,290 --> 01:06:08,385
I was so afraid this was going to happen.

949
01:06:10,128 --> 01:06:12,360
Tarek used to tease me
that I worry too much.

950
01:06:12,429 --> 01:06:13,419
But now...

951
01:06:15,733 --> 01:06:17,669
I just don't know what to do.

952
01:06:19,471 --> 01:06:21,133
I miss him so much.

953
01:06:23,475 --> 01:06:24,500
I'm sorry.

954
01:06:29,814 --> 01:06:30,805
Zainab.

955
01:06:32,317 --> 01:06:34,184
I'd like you to do something for me.

956
01:06:34,253 --> 01:06:38,091
I'd like you to show me
something you and Tarek like to do,

957
01:06:38,157 --> 01:06:39,592
somewhere you like to go.

958
01:06:40,826 --> 01:06:42,557
Like what?

959
01:06:43,596 --> 01:06:45,259
Whatever you like.

960
01:06:45,331 --> 01:06:47,426
Okay.

961
01:06:47,499 --> 01:06:48,832
Okay.

962
01:07:04,852 --> 01:07:06,582
So what is in Staten Island?

963
01:07:07,587 --> 01:07:08,783
I don't know.

964
01:07:08,856 --> 01:07:11,258
We would just go there
and then come back.

965
01:07:11,325 --> 01:07:12,350
We never got off.

966
01:07:12,427 --> 01:07:13,417
Why?

967
01:07:14,862 --> 01:07:15,795
It was free.

968
01:07:15,863 --> 01:07:18,096
We felt like we were going somewhere.

969
01:07:19,533 --> 01:07:23,132
Oh. That's where the Twin Towers were.

970
01:07:23,205 --> 01:07:26,109
I never saw them, but... Tarek did.

971
01:07:27,142 --> 01:07:28,303
Oh. And...

972
01:07:28,377 --> 01:07:29,846
there's the Statue.

973
01:07:30,112 --> 01:07:32,139
And behind that is Ellis Island.

974
01:07:33,249 --> 01:07:36,813
Sometimes Tarek would point at the Statue
and jump up and down

975
01:07:36,885 --> 01:07:39,618
like we're arriving
in New York for the first time.

976
01:07:40,890 --> 01:07:43,292
It was very funny.

977
01:07:45,895 --> 01:07:47,831
Can you go up in the Statue?

978
01:07:47,897 --> 01:07:49,491
Oh, yeah.

979
01:07:49,566 --> 01:07:50,556
I think so.

980
01:07:51,734 --> 01:07:52,793
You haven't been there?

981
01:07:52,869 --> 01:07:53,802
No.

982
01:07:53,870 --> 01:07:54,803
Never?

983
01:07:54,871 --> 01:07:55,839
Nope.

984
01:07:55,906 --> 01:07:57,534
Oh.

985
01:07:58,541 --> 01:07:59,840
Excuse me.

986
01:07:59,910 --> 01:08:00,900
Hello?

987
01:08:01,912 --> 01:08:02,902
Hey, Charles.

988
01:08:04,248 --> 01:08:05,307
What's that?

989
01:08:05,383 --> 01:08:08,583
Um, yeah. I'm still in New York.

990
01:08:10,255 --> 01:08:12,555
I'm sorry, Charles.
I couldn't make it back yesterday.

991
01:08:13,624 --> 01:08:16,255
I said I couldn't make it back!

992
01:08:16,327 --> 01:08:17,728
Well, I'm on a boat.

993
01:08:18,730 --> 01:08:19,823
A boat!

994
01:08:19,898 --> 01:08:22,392
Listen, Charles, I'll explain it to you
when I see you.

995
01:08:22,468 --> 01:08:24,198
But I have to go now,
so I'll call you back.

996
01:08:24,269 --> 01:08:25,260
Bye.

997
01:08:36,949 --> 01:08:38,315
You went on the ferry?

998
01:08:38,383 --> 01:08:39,351
Yes.

999
01:08:39,418 --> 01:08:40,511
No.

1000
01:08:40,587 --> 01:08:42,180
- My mother, too?
- She liked it.

1001
01:08:44,491 --> 01:08:47,895
You know that they don't even have
an outside space here.

1002
01:08:47,961 --> 01:08:50,261
They just have a room
with its roof cut out.

1003
01:08:50,330 --> 01:08:51,559
Really?

1004
01:08:51,630 --> 01:08:53,965
Some crazy stuff, man.

1005
01:08:55,802 --> 01:08:57,236
And they seemed to get along...

1006
01:08:57,304 --> 01:08:58,237
Zainab and my mother?

1007
01:08:58,305 --> 01:09:01,301
Yes. I think your mother
likes her very much.

1008
01:09:04,312 --> 01:09:05,906
My mother's not going home, is she?

1009
01:09:05,980 --> 01:09:07,973
I don't think so.

1010
01:09:09,750 --> 01:09:11,617
I know she's thinking about my father.

1011
01:09:12,820 --> 01:09:13,810
Why?

1012
01:09:16,325 --> 01:09:17,918
He spent seven years in jail in Syria

1013
01:09:17,992 --> 01:09:19,985
because of something
he wrote in the newspaper.

1014
01:09:21,330 --> 01:09:24,792
By the time
they released him, he was very sick.

1015
01:09:26,502 --> 01:09:28,769
He died two months later.

1016
01:09:28,837 --> 01:09:30,328
That's why we moved here.

1017
01:09:34,510 --> 01:09:35,944
Would you like a glass of wine?

1018
01:09:36,011 --> 01:09:37,674
No, thank you.

1019
01:09:48,858 --> 01:09:51,260
Mouna. Um...

1020
01:09:51,329 --> 01:09:55,963
I need to go back to Connecticut
tomorrow, for work. I told Tarek.

1021
01:09:56,033 --> 01:09:57,626
How long will you be gone?

1022
01:09:57,701 --> 01:09:59,762
Um, I don't know yet. I...

1023
01:10:01,038 --> 01:10:03,703
I'll try to get back
and visit him as soon as I can.

1024
01:10:05,709 --> 01:10:08,806
Walter, you don't have
to keep visiting him.

1025
01:10:08,879 --> 01:10:10,040
I'm sure you're busy.

1026
01:10:13,718 --> 01:10:15,051
I'll see what I can do.

1027
01:10:21,726 --> 01:10:22,989
Dinner will be ready soon.

1028
01:10:23,061 --> 01:10:24,758
Oh. Okay.

1029
01:10:38,077 --> 01:10:40,571
Walter. Do you go to Broadway?

1030
01:10:41,682 --> 01:10:42,672
No, not really.

1031
01:10:44,418 --> 01:10:45,613
Tarek sent me the CD

1032
01:10:49,390 --> 01:10:51,087
I think I know every word.

1033
01:10:58,098 --> 01:10:59,829
Tarek is teaching me the drum.

1034
01:11:00,834 --> 01:11:02,701
Really? How is that going?

1035
01:11:03,704 --> 01:11:05,037
Well, I... I sound a lot better

1036
01:11:05,106 --> 01:11:06,506
when he's playing with me.

1037
01:11:12,447 --> 01:11:13,746
How's your teaching?

1038
01:11:14,783 --> 01:11:15,716
My teaching?

1039
01:11:15,783 --> 01:11:16,716
Yes.

1040
01:11:16,784 --> 01:11:17,774
It's fine.

1041
01:11:18,786 --> 01:11:20,449
How many classes do you have?

1042
01:11:21,789 --> 01:11:24,784
Well, I have a lighter schedule
so I can focus on my book.

1043
01:11:25,793 --> 01:11:26,887
Your book?

1044
01:11:26,962 --> 01:11:28,123
What is it about?

1045
01:11:29,632 --> 01:11:33,595
Well, it... covers quite a bit,
so it's hard to explain.

1046
01:11:33,669 --> 01:11:35,069
You're almost finished?

1047
01:11:35,137 --> 01:11:36,902
I'm close.

1048
01:11:36,972 --> 01:11:37,962
Ahem.

1049
01:11:40,644 --> 01:11:42,773
You don't like
to talk about your work?

1050
01:11:42,846 --> 01:11:44,782
Mmm, it's, uh... just not a process

1051
01:11:44,848 --> 01:11:47,478
that's easy to talk about
with somebody who's not a writer.

1052
01:11:52,656 --> 01:11:53,646
Oh.

1053
01:11:59,664 --> 01:12:01,156
I shouldn't have
spoken to you like that.

1054
01:12:02,834 --> 01:12:03,824
It's okay.

1055
01:12:24,189 --> 01:12:25,954
- I'll get it, sir.
- Thanks.

1056
01:12:27,527 --> 01:12:28,620
Well...

1057
01:12:28,695 --> 01:12:31,633
um, you have my number
if you need anything.

1058
01:12:31,698 --> 01:12:33,965
Thank you. I'll be fine.

1059
01:12:35,702 --> 01:12:36,635
Here.

1060
01:12:36,702 --> 01:12:38,137
Thank you.

1061
01:12:38,204 --> 01:12:39,137
Have a safe trip.

1062
01:12:39,205 --> 01:12:40,468
Thanks.

1063
01:12:40,541 --> 01:12:41,474
Good-bye.

1064
01:12:41,542 --> 01:12:43,135
Good-bye.

1065
01:13:18,581 --> 01:13:19,640
Good afternoon.

1066
01:13:26,255 --> 01:13:28,521
Hi, Mouna. It's Walter.

1067
01:13:28,591 --> 01:13:32,258
Uh, no. I was, uh, just checking in
to make sure everything was okay.

1068
01:13:33,929 --> 01:13:35,227
Okay. Oh, good.

1069
01:13:35,499 --> 01:13:37,560
Uh, you know... working.

1070
01:13:40,936 --> 01:13:43,203
Okay. So... good.

1071
01:13:44,708 --> 01:13:46,610
Good night.

1072
01:15:27,850 --> 01:15:28,876
Walter.

1073
01:15:29,886 --> 01:15:31,081
Hello.

1074
01:15:31,153 --> 01:15:33,214
I didn't expect you so soon.

1075
01:15:34,223 --> 01:15:36,125
Um, I just was cleaning a bit.

1076
01:15:41,231 --> 01:15:42,995
I love this CD.

1077
01:15:44,068 --> 01:15:45,093
Is it your wife?

1078
01:15:45,169 --> 01:15:46,194
Yes.

1079
01:15:47,338 --> 01:15:48,830
She was beautiful.

1080
01:15:48,906 --> 01:15:49,999
Thank you.

1081
01:15:53,745 --> 01:15:54,804
These are different glasses?

1082
01:15:54,878 --> 01:15:55,937
Mm-hmm.

1083
01:15:56,014 --> 01:15:56,947
They're new?

1084
01:15:57,014 --> 01:15:58,176
They are, yeah.

1085
01:15:58,250 --> 01:16:00,014
They're nice.

1086
01:16:00,085 --> 01:16:01,178
Thank you.

1087
01:16:03,923 --> 01:16:05,984
I was going to cook some lunch.

1088
01:16:06,058 --> 01:16:07,048
Are you hungry?

1089
01:16:07,125 --> 01:16:09,357
Yes. That would be nice.

1090
01:16:09,427 --> 01:16:10,862
Okay.

1091
01:16:19,105 --> 01:16:20,038
Mouna?

1092
01:16:20,105 --> 01:16:21,164
Yes.

1093
01:16:21,240 --> 01:16:23,210
Mmm, I was wondering.

1094
01:16:23,275 --> 01:16:24,801
Um, uh, Thursday night.

1095
01:16:24,878 --> 01:16:26,039
Do you have any plans?

1096
01:16:27,413 --> 01:16:30,386
No, Walter. I have no plans.

1097
01:16:30,450 --> 01:16:34,185
Okay. Well, then, I thought...
maybe we might do something.

1098
01:16:35,789 --> 01:16:36,951
Okay.

1099
01:16:37,959 --> 01:16:38,949
Okay.

1100
01:16:46,801 --> 01:16:48,828
- They keep moving people.
- To where?

1101
01:16:48,903 --> 01:16:52,070
I don't know. I think
to other detention centers.

1102
01:16:52,139 --> 01:16:53,869
Two Moroccan guys were just moved.

1103
01:16:53,942 --> 01:16:55,410
They had no idea.

1104
01:16:55,476 --> 01:16:57,173
Suddenly, they were just gone.

1105
01:16:57,245 --> 01:16:59,238
Has anyone said anything to you?

1106
01:16:59,313 --> 01:17:01,146
No. No one in here knows anything.

1107
01:17:03,117 --> 01:17:04,107
This is not fair.

1108
01:17:05,152 --> 01:17:06,849
I am not a criminal.

1109
01:17:06,922 --> 01:17:09,223
I have committed no crime.

1110
01:17:09,291 --> 01:17:10,418
What do they think?

1111
01:17:10,492 --> 01:17:12,428
I'm a terrorist?

1112
01:17:12,494 --> 01:17:14,361
There are no terrorists in here.

1113
01:17:14,430 --> 01:17:16,400
The terrorists have money.
They have support.

1114
01:17:16,465 --> 01:17:17,433
This is just not fair.

1115
01:17:17,499 --> 01:17:20,495
- I know.
- How do you know? You're out there.

1116
01:17:35,351 --> 01:17:37,321
I'm sorry. I... Um...

1117
01:17:48,800 --> 01:17:51,134
I sit in here at night, and...

1118
01:17:52,804 --> 01:17:54,467
I keep thinking about Zainab.

1119
01:17:58,343 --> 01:18:01,440
I just want to live my life
and play my music.

1120
01:18:05,217 --> 01:18:06,549
What's so wrong about that?

1121
01:18:14,393 --> 01:18:15,452
Okay.

1122
01:18:16,462 --> 01:18:17,487
Okay. Please do.

1123
01:18:17,563 --> 01:18:18,496
Yeah. Thank you.

1124
01:18:18,564 --> 01:18:19,554
Okay. Bye.

1125
01:18:22,002 --> 01:18:22,992
What did he say?

1126
01:18:23,069 --> 01:18:25,505
That he'd make some calls,

1127
01:18:25,571 --> 01:18:28,510
but they can move him
to another facility at their discretion.

1128
01:18:28,575 --> 01:18:31,137
What facility? Where?

1129
01:18:31,210 --> 01:18:33,306
He said it could be anywhere.

1130
01:18:33,380 --> 01:18:35,509
Upstate Pennsylvania.

1131
01:18:35,582 --> 01:18:37,518
There's even one in Louisiana.

1132
01:18:37,584 --> 01:18:39,178
Louisiana?

1133
01:18:39,253 --> 01:18:40,516
Where they had the floods?

1134
01:18:40,587 --> 01:18:41,577
Mm-hmm.

1135
01:18:41,856 --> 01:18:42,983
But that's too far.

1136
01:18:43,057 --> 01:18:44,252
Yeah.

1137
01:18:46,594 --> 01:18:48,324
Did the lawyer say anything else?

1138
01:18:48,396 --> 01:18:50,593
No. He didn't know anything else.

1139
01:18:54,436 --> 01:18:56,429
It's just like Syria.

1140
01:19:45,157 --> 01:19:46,250
Okay.

1141
01:19:46,324 --> 01:19:48,191
Bye, <i>habibti.</i> Good-bye.

1142
01:19:55,332 --> 01:19:56,596
Sorry to keep you waiting.

1143
01:19:56,668 --> 01:19:58,467
That's okay. How is he?

1144
01:19:58,537 --> 01:20:00,439
He says hello.

1145
01:20:00,505 --> 01:20:03,204
He wants to make sure
you're practicing your drum.

1146
01:20:03,276 --> 01:20:05,337
I am. So...

1147
01:20:06,345 --> 01:20:07,404
You look very nice.

1148
01:20:08,413 --> 01:20:09,939
Thank you.

1149
01:20:10,016 --> 01:20:11,211
You, too.

1150
01:20:11,283 --> 01:20:12,684
Thank you.

1151
01:20:32,206 --> 01:20:34,233
Okay. That's good.

1152
01:20:35,242 --> 01:20:36,175
Thank you, sir.

1153
01:20:37,711 --> 01:20:39,010
You ready?

1154
01:20:39,080 --> 01:20:39,979
For what?

1155
01:20:40,048 --> 01:20:41,175
Well...

1156
01:20:41,248 --> 01:20:43,616
uh, I thought we'd go see this.

1157
01:20:45,687 --> 01:20:46,655
Really?

1158
01:20:46,721 --> 01:20:48,314
Yeah.

1159
01:20:48,389 --> 01:20:49,322
Now?

1160
01:20:49,390 --> 01:20:50,722
Yeah. Is that okay?

1161
01:20:52,228 --> 01:20:54,460
Yes. That's wonderful.

1162
01:20:55,530 --> 01:20:56,463
Thank you.

1163
01:20:56,531 --> 01:20:58,091
I'm so excited.

1164
01:20:59,367 --> 01:21:01,530
Okay. Don't move.

1165
01:21:32,269 --> 01:21:33,237
You know...

1166
01:21:33,304 --> 01:21:36,470
I think that show
was really kind of scary.

1167
01:21:36,539 --> 01:21:38,099
It was a little scary. Yeah.

1168
01:21:38,176 --> 01:21:39,337
Yeah.

1169
01:21:41,212 --> 01:21:42,145
Are you finished?

1170
01:21:42,213 --> 01:21:43,682
Yes. Thank you.

1171
01:21:43,748 --> 01:21:44,681
How was everything?

1172
01:21:44,749 --> 01:21:46,548
- Great.
- Very good.

1173
01:21:46,617 --> 01:21:49,350
Actually, I think
I'd like a glass of wine, please.

1174
01:21:49,421 --> 01:21:51,152
Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't even think to ask.

1175
01:21:51,223 --> 01:21:52,714
It's okay.

1176
01:21:52,791 --> 01:21:55,193
It's not every night
that you see <i>The Phantom.</i>

1177
01:21:56,227 --> 01:21:57,320
I'll have a Cabernet.

1178
01:21:57,395 --> 01:21:58,328
Cabernet.

1179
01:21:58,398 --> 01:21:59,330
Two, please.

1180
01:21:59,398 --> 01:22:00,593
Excellent.

1181
01:22:00,666 --> 01:22:04,367
Well, I haven't been to the theater
in a long time. Me, neither.

1182
01:22:04,436 --> 01:22:07,738
There's a place in Syria called Malula.

1183
01:22:07,806 --> 01:22:10,676
It's a very big outdoor theater.

1184
01:22:10,743 --> 01:22:11,733
It's beautiful.

1185
01:22:11,811 --> 01:22:15,409
We used to take Tarek there
to see concerts.

1186
01:22:15,481 --> 01:22:18,111
- Here you go. Two Cabernets.
- Thank you.

1187
01:22:18,184 --> 01:22:19,813
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1188
01:22:20,820 --> 01:22:21,753
Well.

1189
01:22:21,821 --> 01:22:23,757
Cheers.

1190
01:22:30,164 --> 01:22:31,393
Mmm.

1191
01:22:31,464 --> 01:22:33,731
Mouna. Um...

1192
01:22:35,669 --> 01:22:38,766
I'm taking a leave of absence...
uh, for the rest of the semester.

1193
01:22:38,839 --> 01:22:39,772
Ahem.

1194
01:22:39,840 --> 01:22:41,742
Really? Why?

1195
01:22:41,809 --> 01:22:45,271
Well, I thought I might
spend some more time in New York.

1196
01:22:47,315 --> 01:22:50,584
Walter, you don't
have to do this. You're busy.

1197
01:22:50,652 --> 01:22:52,383
No, I want to.

1198
01:22:53,388 --> 01:22:54,788
But you have to be in Connecticut.

1199
01:22:54,856 --> 01:22:57,293
You have your teaching, your book.

1200
01:22:57,360 --> 01:22:59,421
No, it's fine. Really.

1201
01:22:59,495 --> 01:23:02,467
This is not your problem, Walter.

1202
01:23:03,498 --> 01:23:05,491
It's okay that you're busy.

1203
01:23:08,204 --> 01:23:09,366
I'm not busy.

1204
01:23:11,208 --> 01:23:13,303
Not at all.

1205
01:23:13,377 --> 01:23:17,340
The truth is I haven't done any real work
in a very long time.

1206
01:23:17,414 --> 01:23:20,215
But you just
presented your paper at the conference.

1207
01:23:20,284 --> 01:23:22,778
No. No. No, I didn't even write it.

1208
01:23:22,853 --> 01:23:23,878
I just read it.

1209
01:23:26,556 --> 01:23:28,583
I've been teaching
the same course for 20 years,

1210
01:23:28,658 --> 01:23:30,890
and it... doesn't mean anything to me.

1211
01:23:31,895 --> 01:23:33,364
None of it does.

1212
01:23:36,401 --> 01:23:37,460
I pretend.

1213
01:23:40,738 --> 01:23:43,733
I pretend that I'm busy,
that I'm working, that I'm writing.

1214
01:23:47,579 --> 01:23:49,242
I'm not doing anything.

1215
01:23:55,586 --> 01:23:56,646
I'm sorry.

1216
01:23:57,656 --> 01:23:58,919
Don't be.

1217
01:23:59,191 --> 01:24:01,924
I really appreciate you telling me this.

1218
01:24:08,268 --> 01:24:09,634
Um, Walter.

1219
01:24:11,271 --> 01:24:13,400
What would you do if you didn't teach?

1220
01:24:16,610 --> 01:24:17,942
I don't know.

1221
01:24:18,211 --> 01:24:20,944
It's kind of exciting not to know.

1222
01:24:25,953 --> 01:24:27,444
What time is it?

1223
01:24:27,521 --> 01:24:29,218
Uh, 12:30.

1224
01:24:29,290 --> 01:24:30,884
My God. Is it?

1225
01:24:30,958 --> 01:24:33,555
Yeah. I think that happens
a lot in New York.

1226
01:24:33,627 --> 01:24:34,959
It's...

1227
01:24:35,963 --> 01:24:37,557
Thank you, Walter.

1228
01:24:37,631 --> 01:24:39,692
It was a lovely evening.

1229
01:24:39,767 --> 01:24:43,263
It's the most fun I had in a long time.

1230
01:24:43,338 --> 01:24:45,832
Yeah, I told Tarek
I was taking you tonight, and I did.

1231
01:24:45,908 --> 01:24:47,741
I think he was happy about it.

1232
01:24:48,877 --> 01:24:49,810
Thank you.

1233
01:24:54,650 --> 01:24:55,583
Good night.

1234
01:24:55,651 --> 01:24:56,641
Good night.

1235
01:25:29,687 --> 01:25:31,782
There's a message from Tarek.
Something's wrong.

1236
01:25:31,855 --> 01:25:33,484
What did he say?

1237
01:25:33,557 --> 01:25:35,823
He said they were moving him.
He didn't know what it meant.

1238
01:25:35,894 --> 01:25:37,021
We should go.

1239
01:25:42,867 --> 01:25:44,962
Okay. When do you expect him?

1240
01:25:45,036 --> 01:25:46,471
All right. When he gets in,

1241
01:25:46,539 --> 01:25:48,007
could you have him
call me as soon as possible?

1242
01:25:48,274 --> 01:25:50,540
Uh, please.
It's an emergency. Thank you.

1243
01:25:50,609 --> 01:25:52,306
God, he's still in court.

1244
01:25:52,378 --> 01:25:54,906
Come on, come on,
come on. Can you hurry?

1245
01:25:54,980 --> 01:25:56,642
Sorry, sir.

1246
01:25:56,715 --> 01:25:58,047
I hate this feeling.

1247
01:26:25,079 --> 01:26:28,347
Um... I'm here for bed 38... Tarek Khalil.

1248
01:26:28,416 --> 01:26:30,511
Visiting hours start at 5 p.m.

1249
01:26:30,584 --> 01:26:31,848
What? I'm sorry. Excuse me?

1250
01:26:31,919 --> 01:26:33,980
- Visiting hours are at 5 p.m.
- Oh. Um,

1251
01:26:34,055 --> 01:26:35,080
it... I... I understand.

1252
01:26:35,356 --> 01:26:37,019
But this is e... extremely urgent.

1253
01:26:37,091 --> 01:26:38,355
Could you please check for me?

1254
01:26:41,095 --> 01:26:42,860
Thank you, sir. I appreciate it.

1255
01:26:46,101 --> 01:26:48,094
He is no longer with us.

1256
01:26:49,571 --> 01:26:51,473
Well... wh...

1257
01:26:51,541 --> 01:26:52,566
What does that mean?

1258
01:26:52,641 --> 01:26:54,668
I'm not sure.

1259
01:26:54,743 --> 01:26:55,938
What do you mean you're not su...?

1260
01:26:56,011 --> 01:27:00,043
I mean was he moved to another facility,
another state, what?

1261
01:27:00,116 --> 01:27:01,049
I don't know.

1262
01:27:01,117 --> 01:27:04,385
I just know that that detainee
is no longer at the facility.

1263
01:27:04,454 --> 01:27:07,894
Well, coul... could you please find
someone who... who does know?

1264
01:27:07,957 --> 01:27:09,118
I would appreciate it.

1265
01:27:10,427 --> 01:27:11,588
- Hold on.
- Thank you.

1266
01:27:11,661 --> 01:27:13,027
Thank you very much.

1267
01:27:14,030 --> 01:27:16,057
Yes. Khalil. 38?

1268
01:27:19,136 --> 01:27:20,627
Okay.

1269
01:27:20,704 --> 01:27:21,729
Yes.

1270
01:27:24,475 --> 01:27:25,910
- Sir?
- Yes? Did you find him?

1271
01:27:25,976 --> 01:27:27,069
He's been removed.

1272
01:27:27,144 --> 01:27:28,408
Removed to where?

1273
01:27:28,480 --> 01:27:29,709
Deported.

1274
01:27:29,780 --> 01:27:31,009
Deported?

1275
01:27:32,484 --> 01:27:33,474
When?

1276
01:27:34,486 --> 01:27:35,978
He was deported this morning.

1277
01:27:36,988 --> 01:27:38,149
How can that be?

1278
01:27:39,157 --> 01:27:40,147
No, he...

1279
01:27:47,833 --> 01:27:50,168
Um... sir, is, uh...

1280
01:27:51,170 --> 01:27:53,106
Is there any way that I could contact him?

1281
01:27:53,172 --> 01:27:55,108
I don't think so.

1282
01:27:55,174 --> 01:27:57,975
You don't think so.
What kind of an answer is that?

1283
01:27:58,044 --> 01:28:01,107
I'm sorry, sir.
That's all the information that I have.

1284
01:28:01,180 --> 01:28:02,113
Okay.

1285
01:28:02,181 --> 01:28:04,414
Now, please step away from the window?

1286
01:28:06,152 --> 01:28:09,057
You can contact I.C.
if you have any further questions.

1287
01:28:09,122 --> 01:28:10,522
The number's on the wall.

1288
01:28:13,026 --> 01:28:14,119
Sir?

1289
01:28:14,194 --> 01:28:16,187
Step away from the window, please?

1290
01:28:18,699 --> 01:28:23,971
Sir. For the last time,
step away from the window.

1291
01:28:51,901 --> 01:28:54,668
You can't just take people away like that.

1292
01:28:54,738 --> 01:28:56,172
Do you hear me?

1293
01:28:56,238 --> 01:28:59,541
He was a good man, a good person.

1294
01:29:00,577 --> 01:29:02,069
It's not fair!

1295
01:29:03,580 --> 01:29:05,847
We are not just helpless children!

1296
01:29:07,083 --> 01:29:08,244
He had a life!

1297
01:29:10,253 --> 01:29:11,517
Do you hear me?

1298
01:29:11,589 --> 01:29:14,116
Do... I mean do you hear me?

1299
01:29:16,092 --> 01:29:18,188
What's the matter with you?

1300
01:29:18,262 --> 01:29:19,195
Walter.

1301
01:29:19,263 --> 01:29:20,253
What?

1302
01:29:25,603 --> 01:29:26,936
Let's go.

1303
01:29:32,277 --> 01:29:33,711
Let's go.

1304
01:29:33,779 --> 01:29:35,271
There is nothing we can do.

1305
01:29:37,949 --> 01:29:39,281
Let's go, please?

1306
01:30:02,141 --> 01:30:04,077
He did nothing wrong.

1307
01:31:25,396 --> 01:31:26,659
Are you okay?

1308
01:31:33,405 --> 01:31:37,175
Walter, I need to go back to Syria.

1309
01:31:37,242 --> 01:31:39,178
I should be there for Tarek.

1310
01:31:40,746 --> 01:31:42,010
When are you going?

1311
01:31:42,081 --> 01:31:43,640
Tomorrow.

1312
01:31:43,716 --> 01:31:46,984
It's best for me to be there
as soon as possible.

1313
01:31:49,087 --> 01:31:51,250
You won't be able to come back.

1314
01:31:53,426 --> 01:31:54,416
I know.

1315
01:31:58,098 --> 01:31:59,123
Good night.

1316
01:32:02,101 --> 01:32:03,091
Mouna?

1317
01:32:05,773 --> 01:32:06,763
I'm sorry.

1318
01:32:07,775 --> 01:32:09,438
I am so sorry.

1319
01:32:20,121 --> 01:32:21,111
Yes?

1320
01:33:02,332 --> 01:33:04,894
It's my fault what happened to Tarek.

1321
01:33:07,437 --> 01:33:11,172
We did receive the letter
telling us to leave.

1322
01:33:13,510 --> 01:33:15,036
I threw it away.

1323
01:33:17,849 --> 01:33:19,010
I never told him.

1324
01:33:38,037 --> 01:33:41,408
We were here for three years
before the letter arrived.

1325
01:33:44,376 --> 01:33:45,868
I had found a job.

1326
01:33:48,380 --> 01:33:50,282
Tarek was in school.

1327
01:33:53,386 --> 01:33:56,324
Everybody told me not to worry...

1328
01:33:56,389 --> 01:33:58,416
the government didn't care.

1329
01:34:00,193 --> 01:34:02,060
And it appeared to be true.

1330
01:34:05,065 --> 01:34:06,090
And then...

1331
01:34:07,902 --> 01:34:09,234
after a time...

1332
01:34:10,236 --> 01:34:11,398
you forget.

1333
01:34:15,576 --> 01:34:17,877
You think that you really belong.

1334
01:34:23,418 --> 01:34:24,580
It's not your fault.

1335
01:34:26,922 --> 01:34:28,083
It's not your fault.

1336
01:34:35,597 --> 01:34:36,587
Stop.

1337
01:34:54,118 --> 01:34:57,056
Zainab and I picked it out specially for you.

1338
01:34:57,121 --> 01:34:58,111
Thank you.

1339
01:35:01,959 --> 01:35:04,226
Oh. It's very nice.

1340
01:35:04,295 --> 01:35:05,524
Let me see it.

1341
01:35:12,037 --> 01:35:13,005
I like it.

1342
01:35:13,071 --> 01:35:15,371
- So do I.
- Mmm.

1343
01:35:15,439 --> 01:35:16,407
You look cool.

1344
01:35:16,474 --> 01:35:17,965
Cool?

1345
01:35:21,479 --> 01:35:22,469
Yes.

1346
01:35:23,648 --> 01:35:25,641
You're very cool, Walter.

